description:
Daisy signs Donald up for the US Olympic team tryouts, but will Donald have the right stuff to win a spot on the team?

Contains the stories "U.s Olympic Team Photo Finish", "Lounge Act", "Neighbourhood Watch" Play-Off Contest", Travel Tightwad" and "TV Chef"

This issue was an official licensed product of the U.S Olympic Committee.
name: U.S.Olympic Team Photo Finish

description: All of a sudden, Donald and his nephews are shrunk to the size of insects. They must hurry to Gyro Gearloose, who can return them to their previous size. Pretty fast too, since it`s pretty easy to be stampled by large boots, or get eaten by spiders... By William Van Horn.
name: A Small Matter

description: Mistakenly listed as number 1 by the GCB data base, it was really the 7th and second to last issue.
Last issue, much reduced in size and no color.

The  "holy grail" of Robert Crumb collectors, containing his very first comix work. 
 
To say the least the cheaply printed tabloid comix are almost imposible to find.

description: SKY-RAKER: Part 1 --- Following an Air Pirates, Baloo, Kit, and Wildcat set down on an uncharted desert island where they discover Lily Ravenwood, the daughter of the late Prof. Harrison Ravenwood. She has been here with a special experimental airplane, thought lost for the last two years. Shere Khan had once struggled to obtain the airplane from Ravenwood, and will stop at nothing to get it today.
